This project implements the classic Knight Rider LED running pattern using the LPC2129 (ARM7) microcontroller.

The LEDs move in a scanning pattern (left â†’ right and right â†’ left), similar to the iconic Knight Rider light effect.

A push-button switch is used to dynamically reverse the LED direction during execution.

This project demonstrates real-time control, bit manipulation, and embedded interaction logic.

