ğŸ§  Core Logic Explanation
1ï¸âƒ£ LED Movement

LEDs shift using bitwise operations.

Left shift (<<) for forward direction.

Right shift (>>) for reverse direction.

2ï¸âƒ£ Direction Control

A direction flag variable controls movement.

On button press, direction value is toggled.

3ï¸âƒ£ Switch Handling

Edge detection logic prevents multiple toggles.

Basic debouncing applied.

